						<summary>

						<p>Broken stone lying in a field near the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayāditya, 4th year (699-700 A.D.)</p>						

						<p>Records a gift of land <hi rend="italic">(Pannāsa)</hi> at Peṇukapaṟu to Upekumāra Śarman of Bhāradvāja gōtra by Pullamukki Boḷa Kaṇamayāru, when the Bāṇa king was ruling the Vaṅganūr-<hi rend="italic">Vishaya.</hi></p>						

